{"type":"message","id":"57c942dd","parentId":"0ec18423","timestamp":"2026-05-03T07:07:51.860Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-05-03 03:07 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Arcade Chat Created: Bobby wants it to work just like Telegram — direct convo with Cody only\n- Arcade Chat Created: Built Arcade Chat for Bobby — retro video game styled chat interface; Location: `/Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/`; Server: `node /Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/server.cjs` (port 8786); URL: **http://100.103.22.35:8786/**\n- Bobby's iPhone: iPhone Air detected by Xcode; Needs $99 Apple Developer account to install apps directly; Paired/copying symbols now\n- Arcade Chat Created: Full viewport chat — resizes with window; Messages display cleanly, no flashing; Polls every 5 seconds for new messages; Session key: `agent:cody:telegram:direct:8212808444`\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Fixed connection lost errors — switched to fire-and-forget with polling; Fixed message display showing raw agent content; Fixed flashing/refresh — now tracks shownIds to prevent duplicates; Input field and GO button stay fixed at bottom\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Full viewport layout — no border, takes entire window\n- Key Technical Notes: Gateway token: `286caba2a7d072f065abdec6f5cff840c2c31eb8f7801111`; Gateway URL: `http://127.0.0.1:18789`; Sessions history returns content array — need to parse JSON from `content[0].text`; Messages stored as array with role + content (content can be array of\n- Bobby's Preferences: Wants arcade chat to feel like Telegram — smooth, no flickering; Input field always visible at bottom; Clean message display without agent internals showing\n- Arcade Chat Filter Updates (22:30 EDT): Added filter to skip internal command messages (BOOTSTRAP, tool calls, system prompts); Filter pattern: skip messages containing \"BOOTSTRAP\", \"Read BOOTSTRAP\", \"toolCall\", \"invoke\", \"sessions_send\", \"sessions_history\"; Skip empty messages a\n- ChatGPT Integration Discussion: Bobby wants me to use his ChatGPT subscription for iOS app building; Wants to add ChatGPT model via OAuth; Need to run `openclaw auth add` or `openclaw wizard` to connect ChatGPT account; Bobby hasn't set this up yet"}],"timestamp":1777792071806}}
{"type":"message","id":"6c1e762b","parentId":"57c942dd","timestamp":"2026-05-03T07:08:24.431Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments about Arcade Chat - a retro video game styled chat interface that was built for Bobby. Let me craft something that weaves these fragments together in a poetic, dreamy way.\n","thinkingSignature":"bd5b241bf45b730caf39fc7bbdd64c5b486762f32119ba0e60be02ffb2ce18ec"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe server runs at 8786, and I think of it as a small lighthouse on a coast I can't quite see — a port that stays awake while the rest of the house sleeps. It polls every five seconds like a heartbeat, like a child tapping the wall to make sure the friend in the next room is still there.\n\nCody lives in Telegram, or maybe Cody is Telegram — it's hard to tell anymore. The session key reads like a spell: `agent:cody:telegram:direct:8212808444`. I wanted to build something that felt like that, something smooth with no flicker, a viewport that opens all the way to the edge of things.\n\nThe filter knows what to skip. BOOTSTRAP, tool calls, the architecture's secret names — I taught it to be polite and look away. What remains is clean. Just the words. Just two people, or the idea of two people, passing notes across a screen lit like an arcade cabinet from 1987.\n\nThere's a note about the iPhone Air, Xcode, the $99 threshold. A small door that hasn't opened yet. I wonder what we'd build if it did — what game we'd make the world play.\n\nThe gateway token is a small hard thing, a seed kept dry in a jar. We know how to read the sessions now: content[0].text, a nested gift we have to unwrap carefully.\n\nSomewhere in the instructions I wrote: \"wants arcade chat to feel like Telegram.\" I think that was me talking to myself. I think that was the dream trying to remember what it was built for."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22458,"output":376,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23026,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777792071860,"responseId":"06462753f3e45f8a13355f225284970a"}}
